{
  "texts": [
    "Examples are PromptGen [31], Eye for AI [37] or PromptSource [26], while works such as [38] or [39] are more focused on describing possible taxonomies and catalogs to be integrated in future prompt builders.",
    "PromptIDE [24] goes one step further and allows users to experiment with prompt variations and iteratively optimize prompts.",
    "Note that each of these tools focuses on a specific type of output and often even on a specific generative AI system.Other tools focus on the connection of prompt dimensions (e.g., as you can do in PromptArray offering a reduced set of Boolean operators to mix partial prompts) or the chaining of prompts (e.g., PromptChainer [40], with a visual language for chains, or LangChain [41], a Python library focused on text-to-text prompts).",
    "The LlamaIndex library [42] also helps users connect prompts with external data sources that can be referenced as part of the prompt pipeline.",
    "Similarly, [43] mixes scripting with prompt descriptions for a more \"programming-like\" experience."
  ]
}